{"ts": "2026-06-07T20:16:40.517576+00:00", "update": {"tools": {"messages": [{"type": "tool", "data": {"content": [{"type": "text", "text": "successfully downloaded text file (SHA: e39e158f2cced5a68cc724fd8a0d51b0f066d064)", "id": "lc_868f459b-e92f-4dc2-99dd-2e22d66b91aa"}, {"type": "text", "text": "name: CI\n\non:\n  push:\n    branches: [ \"main\" ]\n  pull_request:\n    branches: [ \"main\" ]\n\npermissions:\n  contents: read\n\njobs:\n  build:\n    runs-on: ubuntu-latest\n\n    steps:\n      - uses: actions/checkout@v3\n      - name: Set up JDK\n        uses: actions/setup-java@v3\n        with:\n          java-version: '21'\n          distribution: 'adopt'\n      - name: Lint\n        uses: gradle/gradle-build-action@67421db6bd0bf253fb4bd25b31ebb98943c375e1\n        with:\n          arguments: checkFormat\n      - name: Test\n        uses: gradle/gradle-build-action@67421db6bd0bf253fb4bd25b31ebb98943c375e1\n        with:\n          arguments: test\n", "id": "lc_b009ba78-3259-48d9-996a-1aee15bf1fad"}], "additional_kwargs": {}, "response_metadata": {}, "type": "tool", "name": "get_file_contents", "id": "6cf02a3f-8fce-432f-9057-c42b607426cb", "tool_call_id": "call_023811424a8440369844f427", "artifact": null, "status": "success"}}]}}}
{"ts": "2026-06-07T20:16:58.604026+00:00", "update": {"model": {"messages": [{"type": "ai", "data": {"content": "Now I have all the information I need. Here's a comprehensive explanation of how testing is organized in this template.\n\n---\n\n## Testing Organization in T03_R02_C02_A01\n\n### Overview\n\nThis is a **Spring Boot multi-module Gradle project** (`spring-boot-java-template`) with a well-structured, tag-based testing strategy that separates tests by purpose using **JUnit 5 tags** and **Gradle test suite targets**.\n\n---\n\n### Named Test Tasks (Test Suite Targets)\n\nDefined in the root `build.gradle` under `testing.suites.test.targets`, every subproject gets **four** distinct test targets:\n\n| Target | Included Tags | Excluded Tags | Purpose |\n|---|---|---|---|\n| **`unitTest`** | *(none — runs everything not excluded)* | `develop`, `context`, `restdocs` | Fast, isolated unit tests |\n| **`contextTest`** | `context` | — | Tests that load the Spring application context |\n| **`restDocsTest`** | `restdocs` | — | Tests that generate REST API documentation snippets |\n| **`developTest`** | `develop` | — | Development-only helper tests (not for CI) |\n\nAll four are registered under the `verification` group so they participate in Gradle's verification lifecycle.\n\n---\n\n### Excluded Tags\n\nTwo key tags are **excluded from the default `test` task** (the bare `./gradlew test`):\n\n```groovy\ntest {\n    useJUnitPlatform {\n        excludeTags 'develop', 'restdocs'\n    }\n}\n```\n\n- **`develop`** — Excluded because these tests are intended only for local developer workflows (e.g., integration tests against local services, exploratory tests). They are **not** meant to run in CI.\n- **`restdocs`** — Excluded from the base `test` task because they are specialized tests that generate Spring REST Docs snippets. They run via the dedicated `restDocsTest` target instead, which feeds into the documentation pipeline.\n\nThe `unitTest` target further excludes **`context`** (on top of `develop` and `restdocs`), ensuring it only runs truly lightweight tests with no Spring context loading.\n\n---\n\n### How CI Differs from Develop-Only Tests\n\n**CI execution** (`.github/workflows/ci.yml`) runs on pushes and PRs to `main`:\n\n```yaml\nsteps:\n  - name: Lint\n    arguments: checkFormat          # Spring Java Format check\n  - name: Test\n    arguments: test                 # Runs the default `test` task\n```\n\nThe CI pipeline runs **`./gradlew test`**, which:\n- **Includes**: unit tests and context tests (everything without a `develop` or `restdocs` tag).\n- **Excludes**: `develop`-tagged tests and `restdocs`-tagged tests.\n\nThis means CI gets fast feedback on correctness without:\n1. Running slow or environment-dependent developer-only tests (`develop`).\n2. Running documentation-generation tests (`restdocs`) that are only needed when building docs.\n\n**Develop-only tests** (`developTest` target) are run **manually** by developers via:\n```\n./gradlew developTest\n```\nThese are never triggered by CI — they exist for local convenience (e.g., testing against a local database, manual smoke tests).\n\n**REST Docs tests** are tied to documentation generation:\n```groovy\ntasks.named('asciidoctor').configure {\n    dependsOn restDocsTest\n}\n```\nThey run when you build documentation (`./gradlew asciidoctor`), producing snippets that Asciidoctor then incorporates into the API docs (placed in `tests/api-docs`).\n\n---\n\n### Summary Diagram\n\n```\n./gradlew test (CI)\n ├── unitTest    → runs all tests EXCEPT develop, context, restdocs\n └── contextTest → runs only @Tag(\"context\") tests\n\n./gradlew developTest (manual/local only)\n └── runs only @Tag(\"develop\") tests\n\n./gradlew restDocsTest (documentation pipeline)\n └── runs only @Tag(\"restdocs\") tests\n └── asciidoctor depends on this\n\n./gradlew checkFormat (CI)\n └── Spring Java Format lint\n```\n\nThis design keeps CI fast and focused, while still providing rich test infrastructure for developers and documentation workflows.", "additional_kwargs": {"refusal": null}, "response_metadata": {"token_usage": {"completion_tokens": 970, "prompt_tokens": 9284, "total_tokens": 10254, "completion_tokens_details": {"accepted_prediction_tokens": null, "audio_tokens": 0, "reasoning_tokens": 38, "rejected_prediction_tokens": null, "image_tokens": 0}, "prompt_tokens_details": {"audio_tokens": 0, "cached_tokens": 8896, "cache_write_tokens": 0, "video_tokens": 0}, "cost": 0, "is_byok": true, "cost_details": {"upstream_inference_cost": 0.0010447056, "upstream_inference_prompt_cost": 0.0002008056, "upstream_inference_completions_cost": 0.0008439}}, "model_provider": "openai", "model_name": "xiaomi/mimo-v2.5-pro-20260422", "system_fingerprint": null, "id": "gen-1780863400-wHy46nV7s8PmGNILgYJQ", "finish_reason": "stop", "logprobs": null}, "type": "ai", "name": null, "id": "lc_run--019ea3ba-fa46-7391-97ab-ac3dbcfb4d8d-0", "tool_calls": [], "invalid_tool_calls": [], "usage_metadata": {"input_tokens": 9284, "output_tokens": 970, "total_tokens": 10254, "input_token_details": {"audio": 0, "cache_read": 8896}, "output_token_details": {"audio": 0, "reasoning": 38}}}}]}}}
